## Explain how to code a fetch request to successfully implemente the GET/POST/PUT/DELETE with JS

In the following example, the `additionalSettings` variable has the key to everything, you can specify the Content-Type, Method, and Body of the request.

```js

const additionalSettings = {
    "headers": {
        "method": "POST",
        "Content-Type": "application/json",
        "body": JSON.stringify(someObject)
    }
}

fetch('url/to/fetch', additionalSettings)
    .then(resp => {
        console.log(resp.ok); // will be tru if the response is successfull
        console.log(resp.status); // the status code = 200 or code = 400 etc.
